Hi, according to the docs, `<span v-text="msg"></span>` should be the same as `<span>{{msg}}</span>`, and by DOM result, it is. However, when trying to build a component like this:

```ts
get childMarkup(): VNode | null {
	return this.$slots.default ? <span>{this.$slots.default}</span> : null;
}
```
I'm running into a problem where `<span>{{msg}}</span>` works as it should, because it's added to the $slots collection, but using `<span v-text="msg"></span>` creates a problem, as it's not added to the $slots collection. I'm not sure whether this is intended or not, but what's the best way of solving this? 

I'm guessing I could just check for the innerText/Html of the element, but I'm hoping there's a better way.

